author: @deggessims
text:
I love that they combined this prank video with actually collecting ideas for the camping ttt, bc they actually did what minghao said in a way with the twist in the camping episode! And all the other games, feast etc. as well!! Then bungee jumping, pd vs. seventeen too! 
I loved their different reactions and how they behaved in a scary situation. (DK’s is hall of fame, Vernon is funny but minghaos was also criminally underrated) , however I definitely don’t think that these situations or clips could be used for something like the MBTI assessment like they did. Getting scared doesn’t automatically mean you’re a coward lol 😂 I mean the way they assessed their own members was very black/white imo and generally I don’t get why so many ppl take the MBTI results so seriously. Like yes it’s a base thing that can help assess a person but the way they did those tests and also now with that prank it’s really not that scientific or their approach def isn’t 😂 like jun and Joshua basically immediately knew something was off but remained silent till they had further prove or didn’t want to seem rude and that was completely taken as them not paying attention etc. 😅 like just someone doesn’t say something at first or doesn’t show it on their face doesn’t mean that there’s no thought behind it

Seventeen and their highlights of this prank : 

S.Coups : Begs the Interviewer to not go because he is too scared

Jun : Singing happy birthday as soon as the lights go off

Mingyu : Talking non-stop even though he is scared as hell
Dokyeom : Runs outside because he didn't know what else to do
Vernon : Being annoyed and continuesly saying he is scared and surprised with 0% energy

Dino : Non-stop shaking and moving his body whenever he's scared

author: @MissMayRandomposts
text: Wow, I can see Seungkwan and Vernon are similar..They pick up things fast and get pissed off when they are scared. Even though they already knew this is a horror edition, they still get pissed off knowing what will happen next and keep saying dont do it dont do it..The difference is the assurance after knowing..like e.g when vernon assured that this horror is not that scary he smiled/ or once he gathered his courage, he was no longer scared and acted thick-skinned. But Seungkwan, he goes with flow, constantly feels scared and can be intensified as the time in the horror place stretches. Simply to say, they both are the same but the difference is the compulsiveness levels. Vernon's compulsiveness level is low, controlled/reserved but Seunkwan's compulsiveness level is high. Because of this, we often mistakenly think they are totally different/opposite people even they, themselves (Vernon and Seunkwan )think they are not the same and not compatible because of this. Sometimes because of this, they can be butt head as Vernon prefers to keep things under control while Seungkwan most likely to intensify things (unconsciously)
